<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="198" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/3305b: Circular telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                    <gloss type="to">All Missions in Europe Except Paris</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T18:00:00-05:00">November 26, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is of high importance that the American Embassy in Paris should be
                            advised of the political developments as they occur in the country to
                            which you are accredited. Accordingly you are instructed to telegraph to
                            the American Embassy in Paris for <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Col.
                                House</persName> copies of your cable despatches to the Department
                            when in your judgment Paris should be so advised. At the end of each
                            cable despatch you should advise the Department whether Paris has been
                            informed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>